/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////// What is scalability in HLD?
What is Scalability in HLD (High Level Design)?

✅ Easiest Definition

> Scalability means the ability of a system to handle increasing users, traffic, and data without slowing down or crashing.



Simple meaning:

Scalability
=
More Users
+
System Still Works Fast

or

Grow without breaking


---

🧠 Real-Life Example

Suppose you own a restaurant.

Initially:

10 Customers
↓
1 Chef

Everything works.

Now:

1000 Customers

One chef cannot handle it.

So you add:

More Chefs
More Tables
More Counters

Restaurant still works.

This is:

Scalability


---

In Software

Suppose your Property Buy/Sell website has:

Day 1:

100 Users

Everything works.

After marketing:

10,00,000 Users

Without scalability:

Server Crash
Slow API
Timeout

With scalability:

Add More Servers
System Continues Running


---

Types of Scalability

1. Vertical Scalability (Scale Up)

Definition

Increase power of existing server.

Example:

CPU ↑
RAM ↑
Storage ↑

Before:

Server
8GB RAM

After:

Server
64GB RAM

Diagram:

One Server
   ↓
Bigger Server

Pros

✅ Easy

Cons

❌ Limited


---

2. Horizontal Scalability (Scale Out)

Definition

Add more servers.

Before:

1 Server

After:

Server 1
Server 2
Server 3

Diagram:

Users
 ↓
Load Balancer
 ↓
Server1
Server2
Server3

Pros

✅ Highly scalable

Cons

❌ More complex


