///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////11. What is a microservices architecture in HLD?
This is one of the most asked System Design (HLD) interview questions.

✅ Easiest Definition

> Microservices Architecture is an architecture where one big application is divided into many small independent services.



Simple meaning:

Microservices
=
Break Big App
Into Small Apps

Each service:

Has its own logic
Has its own database (often)
Can deploy independently
Can scale independently


---

🧠 Real-Life Example

Imagine a shopping mall.

Instead of:

One giant shop

You create:

Clothes Shop

Food Shop

Mobile Shop

Book Shop

Each works independently.

This is:

Microservices


---

Monolith vs Microservices

Monolithic Architecture

Everything inside one application.

Frontend
↓
Single Backend
 ├── Login
 ├── Payment
 ├── Property
 ├── Notification
 └── Search
↓
Single Database

Problem:

Small issue
↓
Whole application affected


---

Microservices Architecture

Split into services.

Frontend
 ↓
API Gateway

 ├── Auth Service
 ├── Property Service
 ├── Payment Service
 ├── Notification Service
 └── Search Service

Each Service
↓
Own Database


