15. Interview Answer (2-Minute Version)
What is Observer Pattern?

Observer Pattern is a behavioral design pattern that defines a one-to-many dependency between objects. When one object (Subject) changes its state, all dependent objects (Observers) are automatically notified and updated.

Example:

In a property-selling application, when a new property is added, Email, SMS, Push Notification, and Admin services are notified automatically. The PropertyService acts as the Subject, while notification services act as Observers.

